<plot>This is a simple film made of, and about, trims: trims of film, trims of art forms, such as the homonymous poem, the song and the picture, and trims of life, namely the postcards hanging on the wall, the duck floating on the water, the childhood photographs, the warm light of a desk lamp. The poem now appears in the collection of writings published as The Graviton, The Millenary Man</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?486532</url></doc>
